description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to join our busy and progressive community children’s nursing team. The post sits in a friendly CCN team that delivers acute, ambulatory and chronic, complex care to children living in London Borough of Ealing. The post is full-time, mainly Mon-Fri, but the team is expanding to weekend service and extended hours, so evening and weekend (including some bank holiday) working will be required in the near future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This challenging and rewarding role offers the opportunity to meet the needs of children, young people and their families within a multidisciplinary inter agency framework.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic forward thinking children’s nurse, with community experience. You will be a highly motivated independent practitioner with sound evidence based skills. The post holder will manage a varied caseload, act as a resource for an identified area of clinical special interest and contribute to the on-going development of the CCN team, lead by the Clinical Team Lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We will offer you clinical supervision, appraisal and support in achieving your professional and personal development plan, as well as peer support from colleagues in similar roles. &lt;br /&gt;Car owner, driver essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameBianca PostelmansJob titleClinical Service Lead Community Specialist Children&#39;s Nursing ServiceEmail addressBianca.postelmans@nhs.netTelephone number07548 142 530Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shabana Razak, Clinical Team Leader Community Children’s Nursing Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on: 07548 141 805 or Shabana.razak@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bianca Postelmans, Clinical Service Lead Community Specialist Children&#39;s Nursing Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on: 07548 142 530 or Bianca.postelmans@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
